The paper is about the third challenge in automatic recognition of facial expressions, which involves the estimation of Action Units occurrence and intensity under different camera views. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, which deals with the analysis and understanding of images and videos. Additionally, the paper focuses on the evaluation protocol, data, and results of a baseline method for both sub-challenges, which suggests that it may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, which deals with the design, evaluation, and implementation of interactive computing systems for human use. The paper may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category, which deals with the processing, analysis, and retrieval of multimedia data, as well as the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, which deals with the retrieval of information from large collections of data. Finally, the paper may be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category, which deals with the development and application of algorithms that enable computers to learn from data.
